      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__xilpdi__apis_1gacf4b60f3bfd29d0d200e4f218b74dcdf" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>int</type>
        <definition>int XilPdi_ValidateChecksum</definition>
        <argsstring>(const void *Buffer, u32 Length)</argsstring>
        <name>XilPdi_ValidateChecksum</name>
        <param>
          <type>const void *</type>
          <declname>Buffer</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>u32</type>
          <declname>Length</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This function is used to validate the word checksum for the Image Header table and Partition Headers. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><verbatim>            Checksum is based on the formula
            Checksum = ~ (X1 + X2 + X3 + .... + Xn)
</verbatim></para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Buffer</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>pointer to the data for which checksum should be calculated </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Length</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>of the buffer for which checksum should be calculated. Last word is taken as expected checksum.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS for successful checksum validation.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_FAILURE if checksum validation fails. </para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Verify the buffer is not empty and has at least 2 values. Otherwise, return XST_FAILURE</para></listitem><listitem><para>Calculate the checksum with the formula below Checksum = ~ (X1 + X2 + X3 + .... + Xn) where X1, X2, ...Xn are data words for which checksum should be calculated</para></listitem><listitem><para>Verify the calculated checksum with the last word (expected checksum) in buffer. If the checksum matches, return XST_SUCCESS. Otherwise, return XST_FAILURE.</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>        </inbodydescription>
