        <name>XilPdi_ValidateImgHdrTbl</name>
        <param>
          <type>const <ref refid="struct_xil_pdi___img_hdr_tbl" kindref="compound">XilPdi_ImgHdrTbl</ref> *</type>
          <declname>ImgHdrTbl</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This function checks the fields of the Image Header Table and validates them. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Image Header Table contains the fields that are common across all the partitions and images.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>ImgHdrTbl</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>pointer to the Image Header Table</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS on successful Image Header Table validation.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XILPDI_ERR_IHT_CHECKSUM if checksum validation fails.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XILPDI_ERR_NO_OF_IMGS if number of images is less than 0 or more than 32.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XILPDI_ERR_NO_OF_PRTNS if number of partitions is less than 0 or more than 32. </para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Calculate the checksum of Image Header Table and compare it with the expected checksum in Image Header Table. If checksum does not match, return XILPDI_ERR_IHT_CHECKSUM error.</para></listitem><listitem><para>Verify the number of images is greater than zero and less than or equal to 32. Otherwise, return XILPDI_ERR_NO_OF_IMAGES error.</para></listitem><listitem><para>Verify the number of partitions is greater than zero and less than or equal to 32. If verification passes, return XST_SUCCESS. Otherwise, return XILPDI_ERR_NO_OF_PRTNS error.</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>        </inbodydescription>
